2.1. From the file-system, copy the project directory to save your 1.2.1 
workspace
2.2  From CDT 2.0, File > Import > Existing Project Into Workspace
*** Bug 65941 has been marked as a duplicate of this bug. ***

Options are now applied only if the builder is installed. For legacy projects 
scanner config builder is installed when auto discovery is enabled for the 
first time.

Reopening.
Verification fails on 2.0.0.200406140300.

Vlad says that I will need to manually turn on Path Discovery for
legacy projects... or at least consider doing so, depending on the
state of my project.

I have raised doc bug 67273 to make sure the user will know this too.

Also, enabling Discovery was not enough to add the Discovery container
to Project Paths > Containers.  I added it manually.

EXPECTED: The container should have been added automatically by either the
Import from 1.2.x or by manually enabling Discovery.
